-- Klepierre to buy Corio, creating 10 billion euro property group
-- By James Regan
-- Tue Jul 29, 2014 03:43AM EDT
-- None



PARIS, July 29 (Reuters) - French shopping mall operator Klepierre <LOIM.PA> has agreed to buy Corio <COR.AS> in a deal it said creates Europe's leading pure-play retail property company, valuing the Dutch real estate group at an enterprise value of 7.2 billion euros ($9.7 billion).

Klepierre is offering 1.14 shares for each Corio share, implying a 15.6 percent premium on Corio's share price on Monday, the companies said in a joint statement. Shares in both stocks were suspended on Tuesday.